---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Ed Barlow — Ed Barlow">
  <section class="home-hero">
    <div class="home-inner">
      <h1 class="home-name">Ed Barlow</h1>
      <div class="home-divider"></div>
      <div class="home-grid">
        <div class="home-body">
<div style="margin:2.25rem 0;padding:1.75rem 1.9rem;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0e1a14 0%,#0e0e1a 58%,#101a28 100%);border:1px solid #2cb67d66;border-radius:12px;box-shadow:0 18px 60px #2cb67d14;">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.6rem;color:#2cb67d;font-size:0.78rem;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;">Featured Presentation</p>
  <h3 style="margin:0 0 0.9rem;font-size:clamp(1.35rem,2.4vw,2rem);font-weight:800;line-height:1.12;color:#f1f5f9;">Read About Drydock: An Agile SDD Development Process</h3>
  <p style="margin:0 0 1.1rem;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;">Drydock is a full specification-driven development PROCESS. You act as Commander and the LLM operates as your Agile best-practice development team.</p>
  <ul style="margin:0 0 1.35rem;padding-left:1.5rem;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.55;">
    <li>Typed Specifications, Dependency Graph, Specification Compression.</li>
    <li>Config Driven Web Console for Commander-to-LLM interaction.</li>
    <li>Context Optimization. Controlled Iteration. .</li>
  </ul>
  <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;align-items:center;">
    <a href="/drydock/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="display:inline-block;text-decoration:none;background:#2cb67d;color:#06120d;border:1px solid #2cb67d;padding:0.65rem 1.1rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:0.03em;text-transform:uppercase;">Open the Drydock Deck ↗</a>
    <a href="/project-docs/drydock/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="display:inline-block;text-decoration:none;border:1px solid #4f9cf9;color:#4f9cf9;padding:0.65rem 1.1rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:700;">Drydock Documentation ↗</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="margin:2.25rem 0;padding:1.5rem 1.75rem;background:#0e0e1a;border:1px solid #252540;border-radius:12px;">
  <h3 style="margin:0 0 1.1rem;font-size:1.15rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.02em;color:#f1f5f9;">Recent White Papers</h3>
  <ul style="list-style:none;margin:0;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.7rem;">
    <li><a href="/iterating-sdd/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:#4f9cf9;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">How to Iterate in Spec Driven Design &#8599;</a><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">How to change the spec and target so you can reproduce — four tries and my choice.</span></li>
    <li><a href="/oneshot/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:#4f9cf9;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">Your Agile Team — SDD Build Model &#8599;</a><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">For small token-count work — an agile workflow for uncertainty management; you are Product Owner.</span></li>
    <li><a href="/marina-aws/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:#4f9cf9;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">The Marina Framework &#8599;</a><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">My big SDD implementation — a trust and sharing architecture on AWS.</span></li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div style="margin:2.25rem 0;padding:1.5rem 1.75rem;background:#0e0e1a;border:1px solid #252540;border-radius:12px;">
  <h3 style="margin:0 0 1.1rem;font-size:1.15rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.02em;color:#f1f5f9;">Project Marina - working but not polished / on hold</h3>
  <p style="margin:0 0 1.1rem;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.6;">The Marina is a Trust and Interoperability platform into which you can "dock" your projects. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Process-Based-Database-Administration-Management-ebook/dp/B073RRQBZC" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:#4f9cf9;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">Process Based Methodology</a> (my book) and scale-proven <a href="https://webcloudstudio.com/project-docs/Specifications/Features.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:#4f9cf9;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">Technology Rules</a> combine to "conform" your projects so they expose/encapsulate capabilities and enable an Enterprise Command Center. I have a working draft built by the prototype for Drydock and this project will resurface when Drydock is done. I could not get the quality i needed from my Drydock Prototype so i am closing those gaps.</p>
  <ul style="list-style:none;margin:0;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.7rem;">
    <li><span style="color:#f1f5f9;font-weight:600;">Project Capabilities Catalog</span><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">Services, Data, Shared Resources.</span></li>
    <li><span style="color:#f1f5f9;font-weight:600;">Agents enforce standards</span><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">Your Stack best practices, Your branding, and Automatic security.</span></li>
    <li><span style="color:#f1f5f9;font-weight:600;">Conformed Documentation</span><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">Consistent docs across all your projects.</span></li>
    <li><span style="color:#f1f5f9;font-weight:600;">Enterprise Command Center</span><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">Logging, Monitoring &amp; Alerting, Scheduling, Pipelines.</span></li>
    <li><span style="color:#f1f5f9;font-weight:600;">AWS Integration</span><span style="display:block;color:#94a3b8;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.5;">Single Library For AWS Service Integration - Built on their ultra low cost services.</span></li>
  </ul>
</div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-photo">
          <img src="/images/portrait.jpg" alt="Ed Barlow" class="portrait" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .home-hero { padding: 3rem 0 4rem; }

    .home-inner {
      max-width: 1280px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .home-name {
      font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .home-divider {
      height: 1px;
      margin: 1.25rem 0 2rem;
      background: #252540;
    }

    .home-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
      grid-template-areas:
        "papers photo"
        "drydock marina";
      gap: 2rem;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .home-body { display: contents; }
    .home-body > :nth-child(1) { grid-area: papers; }
    .home-body > :nth-child(2) { grid-area: drydock; }
    .home-body > :nth-child(3) { grid-area: marina; }

    .home-body > div {
      margin: 0 !important;
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .hero-photo {
      grid-area: photo;
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .portrait {
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
      object-fit: cover;
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid #252540;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 48px rgba(79, 156, 249, 0.08);
      display: block;
    }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .home-grid {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
        grid-template-areas:
          "papers"
          "photo"
          "drydock"
          "marina";
      }
    }

    .home-body p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    }

    .home-body h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    }

    .home-body h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 1.75rem 0 0.6rem;
    }

    .home-body ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .home-body li {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    .home-body li::before {
      content: '—';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .home-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

    .home-body a { color: var(--accent); }
    .home-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .home-body em {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
